$ driverquery.exe

Queries the → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/drivers[drivers] (status and properties) on a system. Usually, they're located under
→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/drivers.

`driverquery.exe` is a command line program and thus can be executed in → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[`cmd.exe`] or → Windows/PowerShell.

It looks as though `driverquery.exe` enumerates the → Windows/registry[registry] keys under
→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Services[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services`] and thus has a relation
to → Windows/services[services].

{ Wide (detailed) output

  By giving the `/v` (= verbose) flag, `driverquery.exe` returns the information in most detailed form.

}
